               <p>ROBERT CECIL sworn. - I live in Mincing-lane: On the 31st of July, about eleven in the morning, as I was crossing <placeName id="t18020918-42-crimeloc222">Gracechurch-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18020918-42-crimeloc222" type="placeName" value="Gracechurch-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18020918-42-crimeloc222" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18020918-42-off220 t18020918-42-crimeloc222"></join>, from one Eastcheap to the other, I felt something at my pocket; I turned round, and saw the prisoner in the act of putting this handkerchief into his bosom, (produced it); I immediately collared him, and took him to the Mansion-house.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18020918-42-person350">
                  JOHN 
                  HODGES
               <interp inst="t18020918-42-person350" type="surname" value="HODGES"></interp>
